Examples

certificate > generate

Request:

<packet>
  <certificate>
    <generate>
      <info>
        <bits>2048</bits>
        <country>RU</country>
        <state>NSO</state>
        <location>Novosibirsk</location>
        <company>Plesk</company>
        <email>info@plesk.com</email>
        <name>plesk.com</name>
      </info>
    </generate>
  </certificate>
</packet>

customer > add

Request:

<packet>
  <customer>
    <add>
      <gen_info>
        <cname>Plesk</cname>
        <pname>John Smith</pname>
        <login>john-unit-test</login>
        <passwd>simple-password</passwd>
        <email>john@smith.com</email>
        <external-id>link:12345</external-id>
        <description>Good guy</description>
      </gen_info>
    </add>
  </customer>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <customer>
    <add>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <id>174</id>
        <guid>e62d4f95-a2ad-42f6-90a2-d263bd7b1a81</guid>
      </result>
    </add>
  </customer>
</packet>

customer > add (2)

Request:

<packet>
  <customer>
    <add>
      <gen_info>
        <pname>John Smith</pname>
        <login>customer-a</login>
        <passwd>simple-password</passwd>
      </gen_info>
    </add>
  </customer>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <customer>
    <add>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <id>177</id>
        <guid>dfdb7ff3-543f-43e5-81d2-3a2583361e79</guid>
      </result>
    </add>
  </customer>
</packet>

customer > del

Request:

<packet>
  <customer>
    <del>
      <filter>
        <id>174</id>
      </filter>
    </del>
  </customer>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <customer>
    <del>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <filter-id>174</filter-id>
        <id>174</id>
      </result>
    </del>
  </customer>
</packet>

customer > del (2)

Request:

<packet>
  <customer>
    <del>
      <filter>
        <login>customer-a</login>
      </filter>
    </del>
  </customer>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <customer>
    <del>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <filter-id>customer-a</filter-id>
        <id>177</id>
      </result>
    </del>
  </customer>
</packet>

customer > get

Request:

<packet>
  <customer>
    <get>
      <filter>
        <id>176</id>
      </filter>
      <dataset>
        <gen_info/>
      </dataset>
    </get>
  </customer>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <customer>
    <get>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <filter-id>176</filter-id>
        <id>176</id>
        <data>
          <gen_info>
            <cr_date>2016-11-13</cr_date>
            <cname>Plesk</cname>
            <pname>John Smith</pname>
            <login>john-unit-test</login>
            <status>0</status>
            <phone/>
            <fax/>
            <email>john@smith.com</email>
            <address/>
            <city/>
            <state/>
            <pcode/>
            <country/>
            <locale>en-US</locale>
            <guid>18b78dd1-2b43-44f7-9599-56ccb56a85dc</guid>
            <owner-login>admin</owner-login>
            <vendor-guid>bec05900-a696-11e6-bf5c-0242ac110002</vendor-guid>
            <external-id>link:12345</external-id>
            <description>Good guy</description>
            <password>$5$DdOOE+q9mEmiBfJ/$/bpsfqL9aH7zxQ1jlrI1jtI95jcD8Y2BHTtqv199CC4</password>
            <password_type>crypt</password_type>
          </gen_info>
        </data>
      </result>
    </get>
  </customer>
</packet>

db_server > get

Request:

<packet>
  <db_server>
    <get>
      <filter>
        <id>1</id>
      </filter>
    </get>
  </db_server>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <db_server>
    <get>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <id>1</id>
        <data>
          <host>localhost</host>
          <port>3306</port>
          <type>mysql</type>
          <admin>admin</admin>
          <status>NO_ERROR</status>
          <db_num>0</db_num>
          <default/>
          <local/>
        </data>
      </result>
    </get>
  </db_server>
</packet>

db_server > get-supported-types

Request:

<packet>
  <db_server>
    <get-supported-types/>
  </db_server>
</packet>

Response:

<packet version="1.6.8.0">
  <db_server>
    <get-supported-types>
      <result>
        <status>ok</status>
        <type>mysql</type>
        <type>postgresql</type>
      </result>
    </get-supported-types>
  </db_server>
</packet>
